1
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:42,041
[TELETHA] He's having a
tough time out there, isn't he?

2
00:02:42,125 --> 00:02:45,125
[KALININ] I believed it would
give him some good experience.

3
00:02:45,208 --> 00:02:47,375
[TELETHA]
Good experience?

4
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:50,583
Even though he returned to the
safe house chained to a chair

5
00:02:50,666 --> 00:02:52,458
with his firearms confiscated

6
00:02:52,541 --> 00:02:54,333
and after being
physically assaulted

7
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:58,041
by the mission objective
and several other civilians?

8
00:02:58,125 --> 00:03:01,416
Still within the allowable
range, Madam Captain.

9
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:03,125
I guess it'll be fine.

10
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:07,625
Sgt. Major Mao and Sgt.
Weber will be there to help him.

11
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:09,708
[TELETHA]
But, tell me Lt. Commander...

12
00:03:09,791 --> 00:03:12,791
How long were we planning
to leave them in Tokyo?

13
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:16,041
[KALININ] As long as it takes
to eliminate the threat.

14
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:19,833
Now that the weight of the
mission has shifted to us,

15
00:03:19,916 --> 00:03:21,458
would I be correct
in assuming that

16
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:23,500
if we make our
secondary objective,

17
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:26,083
we won't need to post a
guard for Miss Chidori?

18
00:03:26,166 --> 00:03:28,625
[KALININ] Yes. Not only Chidori,
but all the other

19
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,916
Whispered candidates
will be safe as well.

20
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,375
They'll all be safe
for a while, anyway...

21
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:38,000
[KALININ]
Yes. For a while...

22
00:03:48,625 --> 00:03:49,583
[KANAME growls]

23
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,083
So, what got him to
come running this time?

24
00:03:57,166 --> 00:03:58,791
Like I'd ever know.

25
00:03:58,875 --> 00:04:00,708
I was carrying this
plaster sculpture for art,

26
00:04:00,791 --> 00:04:02,375
and he just runs into
me shouting something

27
00:04:02,458 --> 00:04:03,750
I can't make out.

28
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:06,208
Can you blame me for not
knowing what he's thinking?

29
00:04:06,291 --> 00:04:07,666
There, there.

30
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:09,750
It was an accident. I slipped.

31
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:12,125
[KANAME groans]

32
00:04:12,208 --> 00:04:14,041
[KANAME]
Right. You just bumped into me.

33
00:04:14,125 --> 00:04:16,916
The sprinting and shouting
had nothing to do with it.

34
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,125
Look, do me a favor
and shut up, okay?

35
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:21,583
[KYOKO giggles]

36
00:04:25,375 --> 00:04:28,208
[KURZ] What's the matter?
You do something bad?

37
00:04:28,291 --> 00:04:29,375
I thought I saw a terrorist

38
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:30,916
attacking Miss Chidori
in the hallway,

39
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,208
but it turned out to be a
plaster sculpture she had made

40
00:04:33,291 --> 00:04:34,750
for art class.

41
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:36,583
She should be coming outside
the school gate any minute now,

42
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:39,625
but I have to stay after
and report to the teacher.

43
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:41,166
Cover for me, will ya?

44
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:43,541
Hey, I'm on it, but don't waste
your time worrying about it.

45
00:04:43,625 --> 00:04:44,333
[SOUSUKE]
I'll try.

46
00:04:44,416 --> 00:04:45,875
[KURZ chuckles]

47
00:04:45,958 --> 00:04:48,083
[MELISSA] Sounds like you're
having a tough time adjusting.

48
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:49,375
Trust me, you're not
the only one

49
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:50,875
still getting used to changes.

50
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:51,958
Huh...?

51
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,125
980 yen?!

52
00:04:54,208 --> 00:04:58,666
Ugh, these Tokyo prices
are deadly! What is the deal?!

53
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:03,708
It's just crab! We're on an
island! Canned freakin' crab?!

54
00:05:03,791 --> 00:05:05,333
You hear me, Kurz?!

55
00:05:16,666 --> 00:05:17,666
[SOUSUKE gasps]

56
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:20,916
[CHIDORI]
Yeah, no kidding.

57
00:05:21,875 --> 00:05:22,875
[SOUSUKE growls]

58
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,000
--[giggling]
--Boo!

59
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:27,916
[BOTH scream]

60
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,500
Oh my god, Maya! You shouldn't
scare people like that!

61
00:05:31,583 --> 00:05:34,166
[MAYA giggles]
So I scared ya, huh?

62
00:05:34,750 --> 00:05:36,791
Come on, let's try to
keep the halls quiet.

63
00:05:36,875 --> 00:05:38,416
Oh, sorry.

64
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:39,083
[ALL]
Huh?

65
00:05:39,166 --> 00:05:40,625
[SOUSUKE growls]

66
00:05:40,708 --> 00:05:42,125
[ALL scream]

67
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:43,416
[TEACHER grunts]

68
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:45,666
[TEACHER screams]

69
00:05:49,583 --> 00:05:50,708
[KANAME sighs]

70
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:57,208
I have never ever had
a new transfer student

71
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:58,958
cause so many problems!

72
00:05:59,041 --> 00:06:00,208
I'm very sorry, ma'am.

73
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:02,041
[TEACHER]
And another thing!

74
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:04,291
You cannot bring toys
like these to school!

75
00:06:04,375 --> 00:06:07,500
I told you yesterday!
Perhaps you've forgotten?!

76
00:06:07,583 --> 00:06:09,500
[TEACHER growls]

77
00:06:09,583 --> 00:06:11,666
No, that gun is not a toy.

78
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:13,750
[TEACHER]
Oh, enough already!

79
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:16,458
[KANAME] So what's with
this hobby of yours?

80
00:06:16,541 --> 00:06:19,625
Do you just like taking pictures
of weird or funny stuff?

81
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:21,625
Uhh... I guess so.

82
00:06:21,708 --> 00:06:25,291
[KANAME] Okay... So why take
pictures of that bozo?

83
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,791
[KYOKO]
Hmm... I dunno.

84
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:29,291
As goofy as he is, watching
him and the way he acts

85
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:32,791
sorta brightens my day.
It's like a breath of fresh air.

86
00:06:32,875 --> 00:06:34,166
Huh...?

87
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:45,583
It seems our angel has finally
decided to go to sleep.

88
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:46,958
Watch what you're doing!

89
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:49,833
[KURZ] I could say the same
to you! Two days, man.

90
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:53,500
You'll be dead by the time
you finish the mission.

91
00:06:53,583 --> 00:06:55,958
Lemme see your back, man.

92
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,041
[KURZ] Y'know, you haven't
run into an enemy yet.

93
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,333
And in two days,

94
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,416
you've fallen down
the stairs, broke a window,

95
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:03,583
knocked over a bookcase
in the library,

96
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:06,500
and generally taken masochism
to a whole new level.

97
00:07:06,583 --> 00:07:08,333
I'm trying to do my best.

98
00:07:08,416 --> 00:07:11,750
Sousuke's point man because he
can do all those crazy stunts.

99
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:14,083
Of course, you should
know that by now.

100
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:15,416
So laugh all you want,

101
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:17,125
but it won't be too funny
if the terrorists attack

102
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:19,666
and he's not running
on all cylinders.

103
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:21,083
[SOUSUKE sighs]

104
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:23,416
[KURZ]
We're probably wasting our time.

105
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,583
I doubt she's
even a real target.

106
00:07:25,666 --> 00:07:28,041
[SOUSUKE] Blind assumptions
lead to trouble, you know?

107
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:30,208
And rabid obsession
leads to stitches.

108
00:07:30,291 --> 00:07:31,875
But... you're a tough guy!

109
00:07:31,958 --> 00:07:33,375
[SOUSUKE grunts]

110
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:37,208
[KURZ] Kaname seems like your
everyday ordinary girl.

111
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:39,750
I mean, sure, she's
pretty and everything,

112
00:07:39,833 --> 00:07:41,958
but her background's
fairly normal.

113
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:44,791
At least, if you compare
it with our backgrounds.

114
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:46,833
[MELISSA] Yeah, teenage
mercenaries aren't exactly

115
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,583
what you'd call normal.

116
00:07:50,666 --> 00:07:52,833
[KURZ] You have to wonder
what good it's doing the KGB

117
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:55,666
to try and kidnap a regular
high school student.

118
00:08:05,208 --> 00:08:07,958
[MAN]
Ooh, chilly isn't it?

119
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:11,625
[KGB OFFICER]
What did you say?

120
00:08:11,708 --> 00:08:15,166
[MAN] Ha, thank you, chief.
It's good to know the KGB

121
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:17,666
employs men of understanding.

122
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,875
[MAN]
That's Mithril's AS.

123
00:08:28,958 --> 00:08:30,833
Though I'm afraid none
of your current models

124
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:32,333
can match it in battle.

125
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:33,541
[KGB CHIEF]
Mithril?

126
00:08:33,625 --> 00:08:35,625
[MAN] A secret mercenary
agency that destroys

127
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:38,625
illegal drug refineries
and terrorist camps.

128
00:08:38,708 --> 00:08:42,125
In their spare time, they defend
nuclear weapons exports.

129
00:08:42,208 --> 00:08:44,625
Their equipment is
roughly ten years ahead

130
00:08:44,708 --> 00:08:46,666
of the Americans
and the Soviets.

131
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:48,708
Their top brass also
has a penchant

132
00:08:48,791 --> 00:08:51,125
for sorting out
regional conflicts.

133
00:08:51,208 --> 00:08:54,583
You know, like champions of
justice or something like that.

134
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:58,375
[KGB CHIEF] So, this Mithril
is the one disrupting my plans?

135
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:01,208
[MAN] My guess is they felt
they couldn't leave you alone.

136
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:03,125
Once a breakthrough is
made in these studies,

137
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:05,000
the power balance
of the entire world

138
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:06,916
will be turned on its head.

139
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,833
Bodies are much more difficult
to come by these days.

140
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:12,166
[KGB CHIEF]
And you want an increase in pay.

141
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:15,916
[MAN] I'm not a communist.
I'm just a simple businessman.

142
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,791
[KGB OFFICER]
We've heard enough from you!

143
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:19,500
There are plenty of
agents in this country

144
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,083
who can take your place!

145
00:09:21,166 --> 00:09:22,291
Maybe you should be thankful

146
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:24,750
that the chief hired
you at all, Chinaman!

147
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:27,791
I'm afraid that I'm not
actually of Chinese descent.

148
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:29,166
[KGB OFFICER]
Who gives a damn?!

149
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:31,416
We'll send you to
coal mines in the Urals

150
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,125
and turn your face black!

151
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:33,875
[KGB OFFICER gasps]

152
00:09:33,958 --> 00:09:37,375
[gunshots, grunting]

153
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:46,041
Now that that's out of the way,
let's get on to business.

154
00:09:46,125 --> 00:09:48,541
I believe we were talking
about securing bodies

155
00:09:48,625 --> 00:09:50,833
for experiments
on the Whispered.

156
00:09:50,916 --> 00:09:54,500
I'm thinking of
kidnapping this girl.

157
00:09:54,583 --> 00:09:56,250
What d'you think?

158
00:09:59,291 --> 00:10:02,375
[MAN]
Mm... Quite pretty, isn't she?

159
00:10:04,708 --> 00:10:08,250
[KANAME] And that is why we
need to decide very soon

160
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:10,958
who is gonna be in charge of
what during the school trip!

161
00:10:11,041 --> 00:10:12,125
[CLASS murmuring]

162
00:10:12,208 --> 00:10:13,375
[KANAME growls]

163
00:10:13,458 --> 00:10:15,166
[KANAME]
Hey, is anybody listening?!

164
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,541
[MALE STUDENT A]
Well, of course we are.

165
00:10:16,625 --> 00:10:18,583
Let's hurry and get it over
with so we can go home!

166
00:10:18,666 --> 00:10:20,458
I can't believe I
actually wanted to become

167
00:10:20,541 --> 00:10:22,500
a stupid class representative...

168
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:24,000
You hang in there, Kaname!

169
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:25,416
Thank you, Kyoko!

170
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,208
And since I figured the class
meeting would dissolve

171
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:29,416
into this anyway...

172
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:30,958
A-ha!

173
00:10:31,041 --> 00:10:33,041
I came totally prepared!

174
00:10:33,125 --> 00:10:34,375
[CLASS gasps]

175
00:10:34,458 --> 00:10:35,875
Oh yeah!

176
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:37,750
I remember seeing you run around
with a memo during recess!

177
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:38,708
Mm-hm!

178
00:10:38,791 --> 00:10:39,916
Good job, Kaname!

179
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,041
Mm-hm!

180
00:10:41,125 --> 00:10:42,375
A model student!

181
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:44,458
Mm-hm!

182
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:46,708
Everyone, just leave it to me!

183
00:10:46,791 --> 00:10:48,125
[CLASS cheers]

184
00:10:48,208 --> 00:10:50,208
Don't you think she's
overdoing it a bit?

185
00:10:50,291 --> 00:10:52,166
Yeah, if she keeps this up,
she's gonna be sick

186
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,708
when it comes time for the trip.

187
00:10:53,791 --> 00:10:54,916
Hey, I can hear you!

188
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,833
Sorry my best friend
is acting so weird...

189
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:59,041
If she weren't so fanatical,
she might have a shot

190
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:01,583
at being Miss Jindai High...

191
00:11:01,666 --> 00:11:03,416
'Kay, please listen
when I call your name.

192
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,416
[GIRLS]
She's on a power trip!

193
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,708
[KANAME] Takada and Tanabe
will be in charge of meals.

194
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:08,333
Got it.

195
00:11:08,416 --> 00:11:09,666
Right!

196
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:11,125
[KANAME] Kaneda and Uchida,
you've got luggage.

197
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:11,875
Me?

198
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:13,291
[UCHIDA]
I'm on luggage?

199
00:11:13,375 --> 00:11:14,708
[KANAME] In charge of
communication, Moori and Mukai.

200
00:11:14,791 --> 00:11:15,416
[MOORI]
Okay!

201
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,750
Yeah, cool, I hear ya.

202
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,208
[KANAME] Sakamoto and Kudo
are in charge of events.

203
00:11:18,291 --> 00:11:19,250
Aye, Captain.

204
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,458
Okay!

205
00:11:20,541 --> 00:11:21,708
[KANAME] And nobody
wanted garbage duty...

206
00:11:21,791 --> 00:11:26,333
So, the only person left is...
Sousuke Sagara.

207
00:11:26,416 --> 00:11:27,958
[CLASS]
Huh?

208
00:11:28,041 --> 00:11:30,625
Is something
the matter, Sousuke?

209
00:11:30,708 --> 00:11:32,458
How come I get that job?

210
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:33,958
Well, our
long-standing tradition

211
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:35,291
at this school has been

212
00:11:35,375 --> 00:11:37,541
that the newcomer
handles all garbage duty.

213
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:41,250
If that's the case,
then I accept it.

214
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:42,625
Good...

215
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:45,250
All right, are there
any objections?

216
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:47,375
[CLASS]
No, ma'am!

217
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:49,041
[KANAME]
Dismissed!

218
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:50,458
[CLASS murmuring]

219
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:52,208
[KYOKO]
Good job, Kaname!

220
00:11:52,291 --> 00:11:53,791
Yes, I suppose.

221
00:11:53,875 --> 00:11:56,375
[KYOKO]
Mm-hm. Well played.

222
00:11:56,458 --> 00:12:04,875
[CLASS murmuring]

223
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:13,333
[MAYUKO] That was so funny!
Did you see Sousuke's face?!

224
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:15,291
[MAYA] He totally believed
that stuff you made up

225
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:17,791
about the new guy
being trash-bitch.

226
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:20,458
All the same, I still feel
a little sorry for the guy.

227
00:12:20,541 --> 00:12:25,333
Yeah, it was a bit of a shock
coming from Miss Perfect here.

228
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:30,166
I dunno what the big problem is!

229
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,625
I mean, Sousuke accepted
the job, didn't he?

230
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:35,041
Would you mind telling me
what you're doing?

231
00:12:35,125 --> 00:12:37,166
Hang on... There's a grease
stain from your thighs

232
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:40,208
that looks like Godzilla...

233
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:41,791
[SOUSUKE]
Okay.

234
00:12:41,875 --> 00:12:43,916
Right now, she's talking with
her friends at a hamburger shop,

235
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,208
but she's not by the window,
so I don't think it's likely

236
00:12:46,291 --> 00:12:47,875
that she'll be
attacked from outside.

237
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:49,875
[KURZ]
Hey, don't sweat it!

238
00:12:49,958 --> 00:12:52,041
Take it easy,
you gotta blend in!

239
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:54,416
But I am... taking it easy.

240
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,208
[KURZ]
Are you?

241
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:56,916
[SOUSUKE gasps]

242
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,333
[KURZ]
What is it?

243
00:12:58,416 --> 00:13:00,208
[SOUSUKE] I've got a suspect.
Suitcase at his feet.

244
00:13:00,291 --> 00:13:01,958
Keeps checking his watch.

245
00:13:02,041 --> 00:13:04,416
It's just like in the
anti-terrorist field manual.

246
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:05,375
Time-bomb.

247
